This is the regular routine but is liable to changes any time W.W. Griswold is our Colonel - Whidaker Lieut Col .George Young Ajutant - [-] Guerris Waldschmdt Major we are encamped on the R.R. but I do not think it is a very pleasant place Daily papers (Baltimore American) come to camp about five oclock letters at seven The boys don't think they will get home now as soon
as they did a week ago but are willing to stay until the Government is done with them for my part I donot think of going home before my year is out but perhaps we will go home in the fall
{2}

warm Co Drill and Target fireing in fore noon battalion drill in afternoon There is a general feeling of Indignation that Sherman should have offered to give Johnson such terms but the [-] action of President Jonhson and the War Department and
departure of Gen Grant for the scene of action assures us that they will have to come to terms such as we are willing to grant
{3}

regimental Inspections in fore noon the afternoon was given to the boys to do as they liked until Dress Parade Tomorrow will be monthly inspection and every thing must be up in good order Boots & guns straps blackened and the men are ordered to wear white gloves but I guess that will not be enforced for some of the men are opposed and the officers do not care
whether they wear them or not unless their orders are imperative on the subject and I guess they will not.
